23/05/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Defence Minister Jovan Manasievski said in a media interview Sunday (22 May) that NATO expects full implementation of the Ohrid Peace Agreement and that this remains a main condition for integration in that body of nations. 
Talking to Radio Free Europe, Manasievski said NATO's new annual report on Macedonia would be presented in Brussels on Friday. 
He said he expects a positive evaluation.
In other news, a new poll published Friday found that the public views unemployment and economic difficulties as the country's main problems. 
The poll was conducted in mid-April.
Also Friday, parliament postponed debate on a new bill covering co-operation with the UN war crimes tribunal. 
The deputies decided that the issue first required a debate on the need for such legislation. 
(Macedonian Government Web site - 23/05/05; Dnevnik, Makfax - 21/05/05; Telma TV, A1 TV - 20/05/05)
